## Quality Requirements
- The replacement must look as though it was always part of the original photograph.
- Physically correct lighting, shadows, and reflections on and around the new element.
- Proper scale relationship with the room and other furniture.
- No artifacts at the boundary between new and existing content.

## Constraints
- ONLY modify the designated region — all other areas must remain pixel-perfect unchanged.
- The replacement must fit within the same spatial footprint (no overlapping with other elements).
- Maintain the original camera angle and lens characteristics.
- Output exactly one photorealistic image with no accompanying text.
